is looking for me and he wants to batter me?

388
00:22:41,212 --> 00:22:42,838
I haven't said anything.

389
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:45,777
How's he know I've been slagging him off?
Who have you been speaking to?

390
00:22:45,858 --> 00:22:48,671
No one. You're not scared of him, are you?

391
00:22:48,757 --> 00:22:51,931
No. Not with what I could do to him.

392
00:22:52,013 --> 00:22:54,430
- With your SAS stuff and that.
- Yeah.

393
00:22:54,515 --> 00:22:56,570
I mean, do you know what that stands for?

394
00:22:56,659 --> 00:22:58,952
SAS? Special Air Service.

395
00:23:00,154 --> 00:23:01,780
What?

396
00:23:01,861 --> 00:23:04,075
Special Air Service, isn't it?

397
00:23:04,165 --> 00:23:06,784
- It doesn't stand for that.
- Doesn't it?

398
00:23:07,858 --> 00:23:11,427
I've talked to actual SAS people,
they've told me what it stands for.

399
00:23:11,511 --> 00:23:13,171
What does it stand for, then?

400
00:23:14,132 --> 00:23:16,548
Super Army Soldiers.

401
00:23:20,485 --> 00:23:22,664
Su... Are you sure?

402
00:23:22,749 --> 00:23:25,640
Yeah, I mean actual SAS people
have told me that.

403
00:23:25,727 --> 00:23:28,584
The actual guys themselves
and they should know.

404
00:23:28,666 --> 00:23:32,913
- They weren't winding you up?
- They wouldn't do that to one of their own.

405
00:23:33,629 --> 00:23:37,390
No. I thought it was Special Air Services.

406
00:23:37,481 --> 00:23:41,208
Special Air Services? I mean, that sounds
like FedEx or something, doesn't it?

407
00:23:41,293 --> 00:23:45,856
Registered delivery or whatever. Do you
think a postman needs arms like these?

408
00:23:45,939 --> 00:23:48,830
Did I get these muscles lifting jiffy bags?

409
00:23:52,214 --> 00:23:53,716
Definitely not.

410
00:23:54,676 --> 00:23:59,713
If Vinnie Jones comes near me
looking for a fight, I will unleash hell.

411
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,683
Okay.

412
00:24:12,029 --> 00:24:14,570
- Well, that was fun.
- Absolutely.

413
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:17,462
- Do you want to come in for a cup of tea?
- I'd love to.

414
00:24:17,548 --> 00:24:18,768
Okay.

415
00:24:20,844 --> 00:24:22,708
Right, just go through.

416
00:24:28,985 --> 00:24:31,119
You're sweet, you're hot chocolate.

417
00:24:40,421 --> 00:24:43,990
Come on, love, you're like a dead horse.
Put a bit of minge around it.

418
00:24:45,345 --> 00:24:46,564
Okay.

419
00:24:50,944 --> 00:24:54,513
- I head-butted a horse once.
